'''Pre-Corellian''' was an ancient pre-[[Corellian/Legends|Corellian]] language from which the most universal intergalactic greeting was obtained. This greeting was ''yaa-yaah'', literally translated as "greetings." This phrase was typically followed by slightly extending one's right hand with the palm opened downward. The opposite was the equally ancient ''haa-yaah'', literally translated as "farewell." The same hand gesture was used, but this time with the head bowed slightly. These greetings and gestures were almost universally understood by air-breathing [[Species/Legends|species]], though [[Ugnaught/Legends|Ugnaughts]] took offense to it; when dealing with them, [[Ebenn Q3 Baobab/Legends|Ebenn Q3 Baobab]] advised instead silently bowing slightly and awaiting a guttural purring in response.<ref name="Galactic Phrase Book & Travel Guide">[[Galactic Phrase Book & Travel Guide (real-life book)|''Galactic Phrase Book & Travel Guide'']]</ref>

The word ''[[Sith/Legends|Sith]]'' could be found in Pre-Corellian lexicons, having the meaning of "due to" or "since."<ref name="Evil Never Dies">{{Hyperspace|url=hyperspace/member/insideronline/88/indexp2.html|text=''Evil Never Dies: The Sith Dynasties''|int=Evil Never Dies: The Sith Dynasties}}</ref>

